---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import toolsData from '../data/tools.json';

const tools = toolsData.tools;
const byId = (slug: string) => tools.find(t => t.slug === slug)!;
const peec = byId('peec-ai');
const otterly = byId('otterly');
const rankscale = byId('rankscale');
const nightwatch = byId('nightwatch');

// Ordering rule, stated on the page: entry price ascending, verified prices first,
// unverified or unpublished prices last. Never affiliate rate. See /who-pays-us/.
const alternatives = [otterly, rankscale, nightwatch];

const checkedOn = '2026-07-14';

const title = "PEEC AI alternatives: pricing and affiliate disclosure";
const description = "PEEC AI vs Otterly, Rankscale, Nightwatch. Verified 2026 pricing and affiliate terms disclosed. PEEC pays us nothing, so no bias in this comparison.";

const schema = [
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    itemListElement: [
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://geooptimised.com/' },
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Peec AI alternatives', item: 'https://geooptimised.com/peec-ai-alternatives/' },
    ],
  },
];
---
<Base title={title} description={description} schema={schema}>
  <section class="wrap pt-14 pb-8">
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="data text-[0.7rem] uppercase tracking-widest mb-6" style="color: var(--muted);">
      <a href="/">Home</a> <span aria-hidden="true">/</span> <span style="color: var(--text);">Peec AI alternatives</span>
    </nav>
    <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-[2.2rem] sm:text-[2.9rem] leading-[1.08] max-w-[22ch]">
      Peec AI alternatives, with the one fact every other list leaves out
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-[64ch] text-[1.08rem]" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
      Peec AI cannot pay this site a penny. We checked <span class="data">peec.ai/affiliate</span> ourselves on
      {checkedOn} and it returns a 404. There is no referral link anywhere in this article, for Peec or for
      anything it competes with, because we are not enrolled in any affiliate programme today. That is what
      makes the ordering below worth reading: nothing here can move for money.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 data text-[0.75rem]" style="color: var(--muted);">
      Checked {checkedOn} &middot; <a class="link" href="/who-pays-us/">our commercial interest in every tool named on this site</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap pb-12">
    <div class="border p-6 sm:p-8" style="border-color: var(--line-strong); background: var(--surface);">
      <p class="data text-[0.62rem] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] mb-3" style="color: var(--muted);">What Peec AI is</p>
      <p class="text-[1rem] mb-4" style="color: var(--text);">
        Peec AI is an AI visibility tracker covering ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini and Google AI Mode. It reports
        on three things: whether a brand appears in an answer ("visibility"), where it appears relative to
        competitors ("position"), and how it is framed ("sentiment"). It separately surfaces "key sources", the
        domains an engine cited to build the answer. That is both measurement types in one product, and the two
        are not the same quantity: see the note below.
      </p>
      <dl class="grid gap-x-6 gap-y-2 text-[0.9rem]" style="grid-template-columns: max-content 1fr;">
        <dt class="data text-[0.62rem] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] pt-0.5" style="color: var(--muted);">Entry price</dt>
        <dd class="data" style="color: var(--g-unreproduced);">{peec.entryPrice}, per third-party review sites</dd>
        <dt class="data text-[0.62rem] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] pt-0.5" style="color: var(--muted);">On peec.ai itself</dt>
        <dd style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          We fetched peec.ai/pricing ourselves on {checkedOn}. It names four tiers, Starter, Pro, Advanced and
          Enterprise, and states none of their prices. Peec does not publish a price ladder on its own site as of
          this check.
        </dd>
        <dt class="data text-[0.62rem] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] pt-0.5" style="color: var(--muted);">Affiliate programme</dt>
        <dd style="color: var(--g-verified);">
          None found. <span class="data">peec.ai/affiliate</span> returns 404 (re-checked {checkedOn}). We also
          checked its Partnerships pages for agencies, creators and media; none describe a commission.
        </dd>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap pb-14">
    <h2 class="font-display text-[1.6rem] font-bold mb-2">The real alternatives</h2>
    <p class="max-w-[64ch] mb-6 text-[0.98rem]" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
      Ordered by verified entry price, lowest first. That is the whole ordering rule, stated so you can check it:
      not by what pays us, since nothing here does today, and not by which one we like. A tool with no verifiable
      published price sits last regardless of what it might cost, because we will not rank on a number we cannot
      check.
    </p>

    <div class="table-scroll border" style="border-color: var(--line-strong); background: var(--surface);">
      <table class="ledger-table !my-0">
        <caption class="sr-only">Peec AI and its alternatives, verified pricing, measurement and what each pays this site</caption>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Tool</th>
            <th scope="col">Entry price</th>
            <th scope="col">Measures</th>
            <th scope="col">Pays us</th>
            <th scope="col">Enrolled?</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="!font-semibold !text-[0.95rem]" style="color: var(--text);">
              <a class="link" href={peec.url} rel="noopener nofollow">Peec AI</a>
            </td>
            <td class="data text-[0.82rem]" style="color: var(--g-unreproduced);">{peec.entryPrice} (third-party; no price on peec.ai itself)</td>
            <td class="text-[0.85rem]">Brand mentions, position and sentiment; separately lists cited source domains</td>
            <td class="data !font-semibold text-[0.85rem]" style="color: var(--g-verified);">NOTHING (no programme exists)</td>
            <td class="data text-[0.8rem]" style="color: var(--muted);">No</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="!font-semibold !text-[0.95rem]" style="color: var(--text);">
              <a class="link" href={otterly.url} rel="noopener nofollow">Otterly.ai</a>
            </td>
            <td class="data text-[0.82rem]">{otterly.entryPrice}</td>
            <td class="text-[0.85rem]">Brand mentions across AI engines; separately tracks which links are referenced</td>
            <td class="data !font-semibold text-[0.85rem]" style="color: var(--text);">{otterly.affiliate.rate}, {otterly.affiliate.model} (programme exists; we are not enrolled)</td>
            <td class="data text-[0.8rem]" style="color: var(--muted);">No</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="!font-semibold !text-[0.95rem]" style="color: var(--text);">
              <a class="link" href={rankscale.url} rel="noopener nofollow">Rankscale</a>
            </td>
            <td class="data text-[0.82rem]">{rankscale.entryPrice}</td>
            <td class="text-[0.85rem]">Brand mentions and share of voice; connects source URLs to visibility gaps</td>
            <td class="data !font-semibold text-[0.85rem]" style="color: var(--text);">{rankscale.affiliate.rate}, {rankscale.affiliate.model} (programme exists; we are not enrolled)</td>
            <td class="data text-[0.8rem]" style="color: var(--muted);">No</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="!font-semibold !text-[0.95rem]" style="color: var(--text);">
              <a class="link" href={nightwatch.url} rel="noopener nofollow">Nightwatch</a>
            </td>
            <td class="data text-[0.82rem]">{nightwatch.entryPrice}</td>
            <td class="text-[0.85rem]">Brand mentions ("AI Visibility Score") and cited sources ("Active Citations"), plus share of voice</td>
            <td class="data !font-semibold text-[0.85rem]" style="color: var(--text);">{nightwatch.affiliate.rate}, {nightwatch.affiliate.model} (programme exists; we are not enrolled, and it would be our best-paying option if we joined one)</td>
            <td class="data text-[0.8rem]" style="color: var(--muted);">No</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-4 text-[0.85rem]" style="color: var(--muted);">
      Full terms, cookie windows and provenance for every row: <a class="link" href="/who-pays-us/">who pays us</a>.
      Rankscale note: a third-party site claims 15% lifetime; the vendor's own affiliate page states 10% for up to
      12 months. We publish the vendor's own figure.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="prose-wrap pb-24 copy">
    <div class="rule pt-10">
      <h2>Brand mentions and citations are not the same measurement</h2>
      <p>
        All four tools above report a "visibility" number, and all four also surface a list of cited domains.
        Those are two different things, and every one of these products blends them into a single dashboard
        without always labelling which is which.
      </p>
      <p>
        A brand mention is the model saying your name in the text of an answer. A citation is a source link the
        model used to build that answer. Semrush's Ghost Citations study, run across 3,981 domain appearances on
        ChatGPT, Gemini, Google AI Overviews and Google AI Mode, found that 61.7% of the time a page was cited as
        a source, the brand name never appeared in the answer text. A tool that only counts mentions misses the
        majority of your actual citation footprint. A tool that only counts citations will show you sources that
        never translate into anyone hearing your name.
      </p>
      <p>
        There is a second reason to treat any single "visibility score" with suspicion: it rarely holds still.
        SparkToro and Gumshoe.ai ran 2,961 prompts across ChatGPT, Claude and Google AI Overviews and found under
        a 1-in-100 chance of the same brand list appearing twice for the identical prompt. A tracker sampling a
        handful of prompts on a schedule is measuring a number that moves for reasons that have nothing to do
        with your marketing. Full grading and sourcing: <a class="link" href="/evidence/#answer-instability">the
        evidence ledger</a>.
      </p>
      <h2>Why Peec cannot pay us</h2>
      <p>
        We looked for a programme three ways: the vendor's dedicated affiliate path, its partnerships pages for
        agencies, creators and media, and a general search for any mention of a commission or referral scheme.
        None exist as of {checkedOn}. That is not a criticism of Peec. It means an article ranking Peec against
        its competitors can be written with nothing riding on where Peec lands, which is rarer in this niche than
        it should be.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[0.9rem]">
        See the full landscape, including suites with AI visibility add-ons, at
        <a class="link" href="/ai-visibility-tools-compared/">every AI visibility tool compared</a>, or the
        specific three-way shortlist at
        <a class="link" href="/otterly-vs-peec-vs-scrunch/">Otterly vs Peec vs Scrunch</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
